&lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; is a 1928 american drama film directed by lucien hubbard . it was the first of three mgm adaptations of the 1924 operetta broadway musical &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . the best-known film adaptation starring nelson eddy and jeanette macdonald was released in 1936 ; another film was released in 1954 . all three versions are set in the canadian wilderness . portions of rudolf friml and herbert stothart 's original score for the broadway musical are utilized in the 1936 and 1954 films , but not for the silent version . this version was filmed on location at yosemite national park .